{\b\f4 Introduction:}{\b\f4 
\par }{\f4 Mile Bones is a Windows card game which simulates a driving trip.  The object of the game is to be the first to reach 700 miles (or 1000 miles under an }{\f4\uldb extension}{\v\f4 extension}{\f4 
).  There are four types of cards that make up the 101 card deck:}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\b\f4 Mileage Cards:}{\b\f4 
\par }{\f4 These come in five distances:  25, 50, 75, 100, and 200 miles.  Playing these (when you can go) will increase your total mileage.}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\b\f4 Hazard Cards (also called "dirt"):}{\b\f4 
\par }{\f4 
The five hazard cards are Out of Gas, Flat Tire, Accident, Speed Limit, and Stop.  You can play these on the computer (if you have them) to hinder the computer's progress towards the 700 or 1000 mile goal.  Of course, the computer can do the same to you!}
{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\b\f4 Remedy Cards:}{\b\f4 
\par }{\f4 These are used to counteract the Hazard cards the computer plays on you (or vice versa).  The five cards are:  Gasoline, Spare Tire, Repairs, End of Limit, and Go.  These cards are only temporary; if you}{\f4 
 use a Go to remove a Stop, the computer can play another Stop on you.}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\b\f4 Safeties:}{\b\f4 
\par }{\f4 
In contrast to the above, Safeties counteract Hazards permanently (well, at least until the current game ends).  Unlike Remedies, Safeties can be played at any time, whether or not a hazard has been played on you.  If you are lucky enough to get and play 
}{\f4 all four Safeties (Extra Tank, Puncture Proof, Driving Ace, and Right of Way) you will be unstoppable!}{\f4 
