\par }{\f4 This is a bit more complex.  At the start of the game, you must either play a Go or Right of Way on your Battle pile before you can play any mileage.  (This is tr}{\f4 
ue throughout the game; you can only play mileage if you have a Go or Right of Way.)}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\i\f4 Mileage Cards:}{\i\f4 
\par }{\f4 You (and the computer) can play only two 200 mile cards in a single game.  Also, if you are under a Speed Limit, you must play mileage of 25 or 50 only.  If you are very close to 700 points (or 1000 if you }{\f4\uldb extended}{\v\f4 extension}{\f4 
 the game) you can only play up to the exact mileage needed to finish the game.  That is, if you have 650 points, you can only }{\f4 play a 25 or 50 mile card since larger mileage cards would put you over 700.}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\i\f4 Remedy Cards:}{\i\f4 
\par }{\f4 
Except for the "Go" card, remedy cards can only be played when the computer has played a Hazard on you.  Once you play a Remedy, you can then play a Go on top of it to continue playing mileage.  If you have previously played a Right of Way, however, you c
}{\f4 an play mileage immediately, since you don't need a Go.}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\i\f4 Safety Cards:}{\i\f4 
\par }{\f4 You can play a Safety card whenever you want.  If you play one during your turn, you get}{\f4  another turn before the computer does.  In a special case, you can also play a Safety before you have even drawn a card.  This is called a Coup Fourr}{
\f4 \'e9}{\f4 
 (or counterattack in English).  If the computer plays "dirt" (a Hazard) on you during its turn, you should not draw a card at the start of your turn, but instead select the correct Safety (an Extra Tank to counter an Out of Gas, for example) and play it 
}{\f4 on your Battle pile.  This will net y}{\f4 ou 400 points instead of the standard 100 for playing a Safety normal}{\f4 
ly.  You will automatically be given two cards off the Draw Deck (if it isn't empty) and it will still be your turn.  You will see a red outline around the Safety when it is displayed on the screen.  The computer can also do a Coup Fourr}{\f4 \'e9}{\f4 
, so be careful.}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 \page }{\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f3\fs20\lang1033 {\fs16\up6 #} extension}}{\fs16\up6  ${\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f3\fs20\lang1033 {\fs16\up6 $} What is an Extension?}}{\fs16\up6  +{\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f3\fs20\lang1033 {
